Glacier National Park¶

This map combines trail and vegetation maps of Glacier National Park. Siyeh Pass, my favorite hike, is red.

def checkSiyeh(trail):
    if "siyeh" in trail.lower():
        return 1
    return 0

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

vegPlot = vegData.plot(cmap="GnBu", column="MAP_DESC", legend=False, figsize=(20, 20))

siyehPlot = siyehLayer.plot(ax=vegPlot, cmap="hsv", column="hasSiyeh", linewidth=20, legend=False)

trailPlot = trailData.plot(ax=vegPlot, cmap = "inferno_r", column="NAME", linewidth=3, legend=False)
trailPlot.set_xticklabels([])
trailPlot.set_yticklabels([])
trailPlot.set_title("Vegetation and Trail Map of Glacier National Park\nCreated by James A. Scharf", fontsize=10, fontstyle='italic')

#credit to this stackoverflow post for the base of the next two lines of code: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/38899190/geopandas-label-polygons
trailData['coords'] = trailData['geometry'].apply(lambda x: x.representative_point().coords[:])
trailData['coords'] = [coords[0] for coords in trailData['coords']]

count = 0
numSiyeh = 0
for idx, row in trailData.iterrows():
    if row["hasSiyeh"] == 1:
        if numSiyeh == 0:
            loc = list(row['coords'])
            loc[1] = loc[1] + 5000
            loc[0] = loc[0] - 1500
            plt.annotate(s=" ".join(row['NAME'].split()[0:2]), xy=loc, horizontalalignment='left', fontstyle="oblique", fontsize = 10, color = "fuchsia", rotation=-60)
            numSiyeh = numSiyeh + 1
        else:
            numSiyeh = numSiyeh + 1
    #elif count % 2 == 0 and row["hasSiyeh"] == 0:
